jobs_results.description:
Our multinational banking and financial services corporation is looking for a seasoned IT Project Manager with proven track record to manage its multi-millionaire IT projects.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Bachelors Degree in Banking and Finance or Computer Science or Information Systems;
• At least 5 years of project management experience: preparation and tracking of budget, plan, committee meetings;
• Proven experience of stakeholder engagement with business users and management;
• Sound knowledge of banking and financial products;
• Experience managing or being part of Project Management Office (PMO);
• Strong verbal and written communication skills;
• Strong critical thinking and analytical skills;
• Must be meticulous in his/her work;
• Ability to work under pressure to meet tight reporting deadlines;
• Can-do attitude, driven and passionate about work.

Desirable Skill(s)
• PMP or 6 Sigma Certification;
• Application development experience;
• Testing and Quality Management experience;
•... Experience managing external vendors and agencies.

Responsibilities
• Responsible for the overall implementation of IT projects;
• Developing project scopes and objectives, involving all relevant stakeholders and ensuring technical feasibility;
• Plan and coordinate project schedules, goals and milestones and make project assignments;
• Create technical documentation and report on progress of project;
• Conduct reviews and manage risks and change control processes;
• Manage the relationship with all stakeholders;
• Perform risk management to minimize project risks;
• Manage the change control processes
